The paper discusses a framework for deep reinforcement learning, which involves optimizing over varying time-horizons and using a shared replay buffer to achieve greater sample efficiency. The use of neuroevolution to generate a single emergent learner also suggests a focus on machine learning and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.RO (Robotics), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
